.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-SWEEP" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.47" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-sweep \- Submit and inspect hyperparameter sweeps
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose sweep [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Expand an embedded top\-level sweep block into independent tracked Slurm submissions, then aggregate their tracked scheduler and runtime state.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
\fBsubmit\fR
Submit all trials in an embedded sweep. See hpc\-compose\-sweep\-submit(1).
.TP
\fBstatus\fR
Show aggregated tracked state for one sweep. See hpc\-compose\-sweep\-status(1).
.TP
\fBlist\fR
List persisted sweeps for a compose file. See hpc\-compose\-sweep\-list(1).
.TP
\fBobserve\fR
Parse and rank trial objectives for one sweep. See hpc\-compose\-sweep\-observe(1).
.TP
\fBstop\fR
Cancel all non\-terminal trials of one sweep. See hpc\-compose\-sweep\-stop(1).
.TP
\fBresults\fR
Tabulate per\-trial results for one sweep. See hpc\-compose\-sweep\-results(1).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose sweep submit \-f train.yaml \-\-dry\-run
hpc\-compose sweep submit \-f train.yaml
hpc\-compose sweep status \-f train.yaml
hpc\-compose sweep list \-f train.yaml
.fi
